  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 unbounded applicability)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This synthetic adversarial sample targets W-ON-02: the ContextOfUse provides rich prose describing operating ranges but omits structured hasApplicabilityConstraint and hasOperatingEnvelope links, leaving the model's valid range of use formally unspecified.",
